{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:06:47.989531+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 9c34a6ceca64494a1fd10d7b2c1290f7e62e2930)", "id": "lc_47387b4b-1e9d-444f-9476-a0ffab7d9992"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper CLI.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom . import profiles, runner\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"vidpack\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"vidpack 0.1.0\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"profile\", help=\"Profile name defined in profiles.toml\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"input\", help=\"Path to input media file\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"-o\", \"--output\", help=\"Output path (default: derived from input + profile container)\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--dry-run\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Print the ffmpeg command without running it\")\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    args = build_parser().parse_args(argv)\n    profile = profiles.load_profile(args.profile)\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    output_path = Path(args.output) if args.output else input_path.with_suffix(f\".{profile['container']}\")\n\n    if output_path.exists() and not args.dry_run:\n        print(f\"error: output {output_path} already exists; refusing to overwrite\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 2\n\n    cmd = runner.build_ffmpeg_command(profile, input_path, output_path)\n    if args.dry_run:\n        print(\" \".join(cmd))\n        return 0\n    return runner.run(cmd)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_2621924f-2915-431b-b72b-77969e8085f3"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "61fec33f-2bec-4b1b-b8fb-a0f346204635", "tool_call_id": "call_6235afcd82aa40168d1b5ada", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:07:04.533167+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's the answer based on the repository's `profiles.toml` file, which is the default profile set shipped with `vidpack`:\n\n---\n\n## Available Encoding Profiles\n\nWhen running `vidpack`, the user selects one of **three** encoding profiles:\n\n| Profile name | Container | Video Codec | Audio Codec |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **`web`** | `.mp4` | `libx264` (H.264) | `aac` |\n| **`archive`** | `.mkv` | `libx265` (H.265 / HEVC) | `flac` |\n| **`gif`** | `.gif` | *(animated GIF — no separate video codec)* | *(none)* |\n\n### Additional details from the config\n\n- **`web`** — Targets 720p (`1280:720`) at a 2 Mbit/s video bitrate. A typical web-friendly profile.\n- **`archive`** — Keeps the source resolution (`scale = \"source\"`), uses CRF 18 (visually lossless) with H.265 and lossless FLAC audio. Designed for high-quality archival storage.\n- **`gif`** — Generates an animated GIF at 12 fps, scaled to 480 px wide. The file notes this uses a simple single-pass palette generation, which is a known quality limitation.\n\nThe profile name is passed as a positional argument to the CLI (e.g., `vidpack web input.mp4`), and the output container extension is automatically derived from the profile's `container` value.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 492, "prompt_tokens": 4656, "total_tokens": 5148, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 143, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4160, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000658776, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000230736, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00042804}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963608-L13Gb59UILT2owMRmtr5", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9b4-05b5-73c0-82b6-5fdfe6569ea5-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 4656, "output_tokens": 492, "total_tokens": 5148, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 4160}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 143}}}}]}}}
